/*🏦 Banking System Backend - Complete Code Understanding

What This Is

A Node.js Express backend for a banking system with user authentication (register, login, logout) and MongoDB storage. It handles user registration with email verification, password encryption, JWT token generation, and session management.


Stack
Language: JavaScript (Node.js)
Framework: Express.js
Database: MongoDB (via Mongoose ODM)
Auth: JWT (JSON Web Tokens)
Password: bcryptjs (hashing)
Email: Nodemailer (Gmail)


📁 How It's Organized
Code
src/
  app.js              Express app setup, middleware config
  config/
    db.js            MongoDB connection setup
    nodemailer.js    Email service configuration
  models/
    user.model.js    User schema with validation & password hashing
  controllers/
    auth.controller.js  Business logic (register, login, logout)
  routes/
    auth.routes.js   API endpoints mapping


🔄 How It Fits Together
Code
User Request (Client)
        ↓
    Express Server (port 3000)
        ↓
    Routes (auth.routes.js) → maps /api/auth/* paths
        ↓
    Controllers (auth.controller.js) → handles business logic
        ↓
    Models (user.model.js) → validates & stores in MongoDB
        ↓
    Database (MongoDB) → persists user data
        ↓
    Response sent back to Client



